New Records: Serhou Guirassy scored the first hat-trick in 2025 Africa Cup of Nations qualifying
Key Match Events: Azzedine Ounahi netted twice, Abde Ezzalzouli, Achraf Hakimi, and Soufiane Rahimi scored one each for Morocco
Miscellaneous Highlights: Morocco equalled the biggest winning margin in 2025 qualifying after South Africa set the benchmark
Others: Morocco qualified automatically for the AFCON as hosts, with the tournament due to start on December 21, 2025, and finish on January 18, 2026
